LIMIT / TOP	Restricts the number of rows returned by a query (LIMIT in MySQL/PostgreSQL, TOP in SQL Server).
ORDER BY	Sorts query results in ascending or descending order.
DISTINCT	Returns only unique values by removing duplicates.
